\subsection{Climatic characterization}
A climatic characterization of the area was carried on thanks to the data in the regional hydrological service of the Tuscany region \parencite{SIRDATIArchivio}. Historic dataset of climatic variables, precipitation and temperature was elaborated for the station: Montecatini V. Cecina [TOS01002131], found at $43^\circ 20' 42.7''N \quad 10^\circ 42' 12.2''W$, and altitude 379 m a.s.l.
Temperature data available was daily maximum and minimum temperature, so the arithmetic mean between these values was taken as representative for the day to complete the climogram, with data from 2008 to 2024. Precipitation dataset presents the total daily precipitations in the area, data was available from 2006 to 2024.  \\


\begin{figure} [ht!]
	\centering
	\includegraphics[width=1\linewidth]{Images/Precipitations.png}
	\caption{Total annual precipitation for every year within 2009 and 2024, allover mean is 956mm}
	\label{fig:Precipitation}
	
\end{figure}

Precipitation in the past 15 years have been stable, around 950 mm/year, value that is representative for a Mediterranean environment at around 400 m of altitude. There is no evident trend of decreasing precipitation often consequence of climate warming in the time period concerned. The standard deviation is 237 mm over a mean of 956 mm indicating moderate variability, most years' values are concentrated between 700 and 1200 mm (\Cref{fig:Precipitation}). \\

\begin{figure} [ht!]
	\centering
	\includegraphics[width=1\linewidth]{Images/Temperatures.png}
	\caption{Yearly mean temperatures, within 2009 and 2024, allover mean is 15.2°C}
	\label{fig:Temperatures}
	
\end{figure}

Temperatures don't show any evident warming trend either, the mean temperature of these years is 15.2°C and the standard deviation is 0.5. Variability is low, all years are between 14,7°C and 15,7°C, with the only anomalies in 2010 (13,80°C) and in 2022 (16,11°C), that with -1.4 and +1.7 standard deviation are anomalous values compared to the historical mean. These temperature values too reflect well the typical Mediterranean climate at this elevation (\Cref{fig:Temperatures}). \\



\begin{figure} [ht!]
	\centering
	\includegraphics[width=1\linewidth]{Images/Climogram.png}
	\caption{Climogram that describes the monthly variation of total monthly precipitation in millimeters (mm) and mean monthly temperature in Celsius degrees (°C)}
	\label{fig:Climogram}
	
