Considering seasonal variability in summer the temperature peaks around 25°C in August, while precipitation drops to its lowest around 20 mm. In winter months temperature is under 10°C, while precipitations are relatively high, 80–100 mm, especially in December and January (\Cref{fig:Climogram}). The mildening effect of the proximity to the coastline is evident in the seasonal patterns of temperatures and precipitations. 

