\subparagraph{Maquis} 
Two Maquis areas are considered, these are characterized by woody vegetation, they represent the margin of cultivated fields and the community is mainly composed by shrubs. In \Cref{fig:Transects} these sites are represented by the green areas.

\subparagraph{Meadow}
Two Meadow areas are considered, these are grassland areas between fields or roads often cultivated, grass represented mostly by annual plants flowering in spring. During the study they underwent mowing from the agricultural management, with which most flowers were cut off, limiting the data available. In \Cref{fig:Transects} they are represented by the yellow areas.

\subparagraph{Riparian} 
One riparian area was included in the study. It is an area along a canal formed by a river with torrential character. It was found to be completely dry during August and July, for the rest of the year, the canal maintains only a minimal base flow. In \Cref{fig:Transects} the riparian area is represented by the blue area.

